When working under `ts/`, read `ts/CLAUDE.md` first for local detail (key
paths, entry points, the dev loop, and ankountant UI guidance).
Most important gotcha: pages are client-only (SSR/prerender off) and talk to
the Rust backend through `postProto()` against `@generated/backend`, which is
codegen'd from `proto/` into `out/` — rebuild after any `.proto` change.
